    "This limitation affects its ability to provide contextually rich and experientially informed responses.",
    "The case of Helen Keller is illustrative.",
    "Despite her sensory limitations, she was able to ground language in her experiences through her remaining sensorimotor capacities.",
    "This grounding provided a basis for understanding and interacting with the world, which was then expanded through language.",
    "Keller's ability to learn and ground language was facilitated by her direct, albeit limited, sensorimotor interactions with her environment, something GPT-4 inherently lacks."
